---

<Base
  title="Kybella Injections in Houston | The Oaks Plastic Surgery"
  description="Kybella Injections in Houston at The Oaks Plastic Surgery. Board-certified plastic surgeons offering personalized care."
  headerTitle="Kybella Injections in Houston"
  headerImage="/img/neck-lift-hero.jpg"
  headerMarginBottom={60}
  canonical="https://theoaksplasticsurgery.com/kybella-houston"
>
<section class="mb-0">
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-lg-8 offset-lg-2">
                            <p class="wow fadeInUp lead text-center">
                                We all know that both men and women desire a well-defined jawline. Not long ago, liposuction was one of the only options for treating a double chin (submental fat). Then came the breakthrough, non-surgical procedure, Kybella. Time and time again, Kybella proves to be the #1 injection for double-chin treatment.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
            <section class="mb-0">
                <div class="container-fluid">
                    
                </div>
            </section>
            <section class="text-section pb-240">
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row">
                        <h2 class="wow fadeInUp center text-center"> </h2>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div data-jarallax-element="-150" class="text-section-box"></div>
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="row text-row">
                        <div class="col-lg-6">
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>Who Qualifies for Kybella Injections?</h3>
                                <p>
                                    Adults with moderate to severe amounts of submental fat are ideal Kybella injection candidates. Disqualifying factors include:
                                </p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>If you have difficulty swallowing</li>
                                    <li>If you are pregnant, or nursing</li>
                                    <li>Have chin or neck related medical issues</li>
                                </ul>
                                <p>If you qualify for Kybella injections, TOPS’ highly-qualified staff members will build out a treatment plan, designed specifically for your needs. TOPS staff will inquire about your medical history, including any past cosmetic procedures to make sure that the procedure is done safely and without side effects. </p>
                                <p>Interested in Kybella injections? Our injection specialists are eager to help you achieve a more contoured chin. Interested in Kybella injections? Our injection specialists are eager to help you achieve a more contoured chin. <a href="/contact-us">Schedule an appointment today</a>.</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>What procedures are often performed with Kybella?</h3>
                                <p>
                                    Kybella injections work best with other complimenting procedures at The Oaks Plastic Surgery. Kybella injections give you a sculpted chin but don't tighten skin or eliminate wrinkles. That is why many patients will opt for <a href="/houston-botox">Botox</a> as well.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    Since Kybella injections are not suggested for combating fat on other areas of the body, the Oaks Plastic Surgery often performs <a href="/liposuction-houston">liposuction</a> for fat around the body. For fat around the face, TOPS surgeons perform <a href="/buccal-fat-removal">Buccal fat removal</a>.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="col-lg-6 pt-lg-5">
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>What can you expect during your first consultation for Kybella?</h3>
                                <p class="align-content-end">
                                    If interested in Kybella treatment in Houston, schedule an appointment with <a href="/danielle-andry-houston">Dr. Danielle Andry</a> or <a href="/nandi-wijay-houston">Dr. Nandi Wijay</a>.
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    At The Oaks Plastic Surgery, you can expect the initial consultation to last an hour or more. In your consultation, your Houston plastic surgeon will:
                                </p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>Learn about your specific requests and goals</li>
                                    <li>Perform a thorough examination, focusing on your individual anatomy.</li>
                                    <li>Discuss if you are a good candidate for Kybella treatment.</li>
                                    <li>Outline the potential risks of Kybella treatment for you.</li>
                                    <li>Ample opportunity for questions about the Kybella procedure or any other cosmetic procedure.</li>
                                    <li>With your permission, we will take before and after pictures.</li>
                                    <li>Sensitive to needles? TOPS staff has many techniques to decrease discomfort during the procedure.</li>
                                    <li>We understand many patients have busy lives. That is why the cosmetic surgeons at TOPS streamline the process. Our team can accommodate your busy life, so <a href="/contact-us">schedule an appointment with us today</a>.</li>
                                </ul>                                
                            </div>
                            <div class="text-section-block">
                                <h3>What can you expect the day of your Kybella procedure?</h3>
                                <p class="align-content-end">
                                    After greetings at the front desk at our Houston office, you will go to one of the cosmetic procedure rooms. If you have a needle sensitivity, TOPS staff can apply a topical numbing cream. Your Kybella specialist will discuss your specific treatment plan and aesthetic goals. The plastic surgeons at TOPS pride themselves in offering individualized non-surgical cosmetic treatments. TOPS also has experienced nurse practitioners, who perform Kybella treatments and <a href="/fillers-houston">other fillers</a> in Houston.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
